</p><p><b>Chicken tikka</b> is a chicken dish originating in the Punjab reg=
ion of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Cuisine_of_Ind=
ia" title=3D"Cookbook:Cuisine of India">Indian Subcontinent</a> made by bak=
ing <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Chicken" title=3D"Coo=
kbook:Chicken">chicken</a> which has been <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.o=
rg/wiki/Cookbook:Marinating" title=3D"Cookbook:Marinating">marinated</a> in=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Spices_and_herbs" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Spices and herbs">spices</a> and <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Yogurt" title=3D"Cookbook:Yogurt=
">yoghurt</a>. It should not be confused with <a href=3D"https://en.wikiboo=
ks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Chicken_Tikka_Masala" title=3D"Cookbook:Chicken Tikka =
Masala">Chicken Tikka Masala</a> (of which it is an ingredient). It is trad=
itionally cooked on <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Skewe=
r" title=3D"Cookbook:Skewer">skewers</a> in a <a href=3D"https://en.wikiboo=
ks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tandoor" title=3D"Cookbook:Tandoor">tandoor</a> and is=
 usually boneless. It is tasty when served with yellow rice and a spicy sal=
ad.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Ingredients">Ingredients</h=
2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/w/index.php?title=3DCookbook:Chick=
en_Tikka&amp;veaction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Ingred=
ients" class=3D"mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span cla=
ss=3D"mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org=
/w/index.php?title=3DCookbook:Chicken_Tikka&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=
=3D1" title=3D"Edit section's source code: Ingredients"><span>edit source</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<ul><li>675 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:G" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:G">g</a> (1.5 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks=
.org/wiki/Cookbook:Pound" title=3D"Cookbook:Pound">lb</a>) skinless and bon=
eless <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Chicken#Breast" tit=
le=3D"Cookbook:Chicken">chicken breast</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks=
.org/wiki/Cookbook:Dice" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Dice">dice=
d</a> into cubes</li>
<li>1 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tablespoon" title=
=3D"Cookbook:Tablespoon">tbsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/=
Cookbook:Mustard" title=3D"Cookbook:Mustard">mustard</a> seed oil (see note=
s)</li>
<li>50 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:ML" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Cookbook:ML">ml</a> (2 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org=
/wiki/Cookbook:Fluid_Ounce" title=3D"Cookbook:Fluid Ounce">fl oz</a>) <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Milk" title=3D"Cookbook:Milk">=
milk</a></li>
<li>150 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:ML" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"Cookbook:ML">ml</a> (5 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.or=
g/wiki/Cookbook:Fluid_Ounce" title=3D"Cookbook:Fluid Ounce">fl oz</a>) natu=
ral <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Yogurt" title=3D"Cook=
book:Yogurt">yoghurt</a></li>
<li>2 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tablespoon" title=
=3D"Cookbook:Tablespoon">tbsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/=
Cookbook:Lemon_Juice" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Lemon Juice">=
lemon juice</a></li>
<li>1 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tablespoon" title=
=3D"Cookbook:Tablespoon">tbsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/=
Cookbook:Tomato_Paste" title=3D"Cookbook:Tomato Paste">tomato paste</a></li=
>
<li>2 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tablespoon" title=
=3D"Cookbook:Tablespoon">tbsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/=
Cookbook:Chopping" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Chopping">choppe=
d</a> fresh <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Cilantro" tit=
le=3D"Cookbook:Cilantro">cilantro</a> (coriander leaves)</li>
<li>4 large cloves of <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Gar=
lic" title=3D"Cookbook:Garlic">garlic</a>, finely <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Chop" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Chop=
">chopped</a></li>
<li>1=E2=80=934 chopped fresh red <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/=
Cookbook:Chili_Pepper" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cookbook:Chili Pepper=
">chillis</a> (depending on strength of the chillis and the desired strengt=
h of the marinade)</li>
<li>2 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Teaspoon" title=3D"=
Cookbook:Teaspoon">tsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookboo=
k:Paprika" title=3D"Cookbook:Paprika">paprika</a></li>
<li>2 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Teaspoon" title=3D"=
Cookbook:Teaspoon">tsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookboo=
k:Garam_Masala" title=3D"Cookbook:Garam Masala">garam masala</a></li>
<li>1 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Teaspoon" title=3D"=
Cookbook:Teaspoon">tsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookboo=
k:Cumin" title=3D"Cookbook:Cumin">cumin</a> powder</li>
<li>=C2=BD <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Teaspoon" titl=
e=3D"Cookbook:Teaspoon">tsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Co=
okbook:Turmeric" title=3D"Cookbook:Turmeric">turmeric</a></li>
<li>1 <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Teaspoon" title=3D"=
Cookbook:Teaspoon">tsp</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookboo=
k:Salt" title=3D"Cookbook:Salt">salt</a> (use rock salt for best results)</=
li></ul>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Procedure">Procedure</h2><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/w/index.php?title=3DCookbook:Chicken_T=
ikka&amp;veaction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Procedure"=
 class=3D"mw-editsection-visualeditor"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"=
mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/w/ind=
ex.php?title=3DCookbook:Chicken_Tikka&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" ti=
tle=3D"Edit section's source code: Procedure"><span>edit source</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<ol><li>Add all of the ingredients except the chicken to a non-metallic <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Mixing_Bowl" title=3D"Cookbo=
ok:Mixing Bowl">mixing bowl</a>, and mix well.</li>
<li>Add the chicken and mix until fully coated.</li>
<li>Ideally, the chicken should now be left in a refrigerator to <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Marinating" title=3D"Cookbook:Marin=
ating">marinate</a> for at least 24 hours. It may not be safe to leave chic=
ken which has previously been frozen for longer than 24 hours, but fresh ch=
icken should be left to marinate for 48 hours for best results. If you do n=
ot wish to leave the chicken to marinate, simply continue to the next step.=
</li>
<li>For best results, place on skewers and cook in a <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Tandoor" title=3D"Cookbook:Tandoor">tandoor</a>=
 or ceramic pot oven. The chicken can also be cooked on skewers under a med=
ium <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Grilling" title=3D"Co=
okbook:Grilling">grill</a> for 5=E2=80=938 minutes on each side or barbecue=
d (cooking times depend on the temperature of the barbecue). Always ensure =
the chicken is cooked throughout before serving. It should come apart easil=
y when pressed down with the side of a fork.</li>
<li>Serve with <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Naan" titl=
e=3D"Cookbook:Naan">naan</a>, with <a href=3D"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki=
/Cookbook:Rice" title=3D"Cookbook:Rice">rice</a> or use in a <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Cookbook:Chicken_Tikka_Masala" title=3D"Cookbook=
:Chicken Tikka Masala">Chicken Tikka Masala</a>.</li></ol>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Notes,_tips,_and_variations=
"><span id=3D"Notes.2C_tips.2C_and_variations"></span>Notes, tips, and vari=
ations</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
